comments: Kispert (WAS) firms up in Schroder's (BKN) path and does not deliver any illegal contact when setting the pick.
Claxton (BKN) brings his forearm down, and marginal contact occurs with Gill's (WAS) legal forearm off ball.
Poole (WAS) briefly grasps Claxton's (BKN) arm before immediately releasing his arm off ball.
Gill (WAS) brings his arms forward into Schroder's (BKN) front and initiates contact that affects Schroder's SQBR.
Kuzma (WAS) avoids making contact with Claxton (BKN) during the shot attempt in the post.
Finney-Smith's (BKN) right foot comes down out of bounds while he is in possession of the ball. Possession is properly awarded to Washington.
Thomas (BKN) cleanly deflects Poole's (WAS) pass, and any ensuing arm contact is incidental.
Claxton's (BKN) arms come out slightly as he firms up in Avdija's (WAS) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the pick.

Gill (WAS) moves alongside Thomas' (BKN) path and absorbs the contact after his gather. Gill then brushes Thomas' left arm as he is retreating his right hand away from his path, and the contact is marginal.
Gill (WAS) firms up in Bridges' (BKN) path and does not deliver any illegal contact when setting the pick.
Claxton (BKN) moves alongside Avdija's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact prior to cleanly blocking the driving shot attempt.
Claxton (BKN) establishes himself in Avdija's (WAS) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the pick.
Gill (WAS) legally contests Schroder's (BKN) jump shot attempt.
Claxton (BKN) moves alongside Poole's (WAS) path and avoids making illegal contact with the offensive player during the driving shot attempt.
Kuzma's (WAS) off-arm comes out slightly as he gathers the ball and changes the direction of his drive and marginal contact occurs with Finney-Smith's (BKN) side.
Avdija (WAS) comes together with Thomas (BKN) as the screen is set and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Poole (WAS) grabs and pulls Thomas' (BKN) left arm, which affects his ability to get to the pass.
Thomas (BKN) and Poole (WAS) come together off-ball and the marginal contact dissolves shortly thereafter.
Poole (WAS) moves alongside Schroder's (BKN) path and the contact during the driving shot attempt is marginal.
Bagley III (WAS) cleanly blocks Schroder's (BKN) shot attempt before the ball touches the backboard or reaches its apex.
Schroder (BKN) steps into Poole's (WAS) path and leg to leg contact occurs, which trips Poole during his drive.
Claxton (BKN) and Bagley III (WAS) come together during the rebounding opportunity and the contact is marginal.
Thomas (BKN) establishes the ball in the frontcourt prior to eight seconds passing after Brooklyn gained possession.
Bagley III (WAS) brings himself underneath the basket and marginal body contact occurs with Thomas (BKN) after the release of his driving shot attempt.

Thomas (BKN) releases his driving shot attempt and his left arm comes down as he returns to the floor, and marginal contact occurs with Bagley III's (WAS) head/face. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Avdija (WAS) rests his forearm on Thomas' (BKN) back as he moves alongside Thomas' path and the contact after Thomas' gather into the driving shot attempt is marginal.
Thomas (BKN) falls to the floor after his driving shot attempt and lower body contact occurs with Kispert (WAS), which impacts his abiity to secure the rebound and return to the floor.
Kuzma (WAS) commits a take foul on Schroder (BKN). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Bagley III (WAS) firms up over his right leg and establishes himself in Schroder's (BKN) path, and does not deliver illegal contact.
Kuzma (WAS) commits a take foul on Finney-Smith (BKN). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Bridges (BKN) brings his arm down toward the ball and marginal contact occurs with Avdija's (WAS) arm as he secures the rebound.
Schroder (BKN) brings his arms toward the ball and marginal brush contact occurs with Avdija (WAS) at the beginning of his dribble in transition.
Finney-Smith (BKN) brings his hand directly to the ball and cleanly deflects it away from Avdija (WAS) during his transition drive.
